        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 9:40PM CDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 940 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Hoxie, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Hoxie around 945 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
